course.subject: MATH
course.name: Planetary Science
course.description: This course presents the fundamentals of planetary science. Scientific principles and application of mathematical techniques for studying solar system bodies are to be introduced. Topics include characteristics of planets (atmosphere, surface, interior), celestial mechanics and astrodynamics, planet formation, and exoplanets.
course.prerequisites: MATH 2010/2011/2021/2023 AND PHYS 1111/1112/1152/1312
